AS Mzansi was
celebrating the new year on 02 January, firefighters were battling a huge fire
in Parliament. Parts of Parliament,
including the National Assembly, were destroyed by fire. After the case was
postponed, the alleged arsonist Zandile Christmas Mafe will appear in the Cape
Town Magistrates Court on Tuesday, 11 January. The state requested
more time to prepare and investigate further in order to confirm his residence. Mafe was nabbed by
police in the Parliament precinct around dawn on Sunday, 02 December, after a
fire broke out on the premises. He is facing charges
of theft, housebreaking, and arson and will be charged under the National Key
Point Act.